Here‚Äôs a photo of me, receiving my first ever award during an agency townhall meeting back in 2017.

A little bit of my journey leading up to that moment.

After NS, I stepped into Insurance straight. I heard it's sales and I can earn a lot of money, so why not? ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

But I had my struggles in the initial 8 months. I was only earning $1.8k in total. I almost gave up (I was in debt during that time as well).

Looking back, I‚Äôm glad I didn't give up. I feel that credit for my career breakthrough goes to both ‚Äúperseverance‚Äù and ‚Äúluck‚Äù. Breakthrough is something you have to be ready for, and when the element of luck comes, you break through. Breakthrough doesn‚Äôt come ‚Äújust like that‚Äù because you learn and worked hard.¬†

Since then, warm cases started to come in and I earned my first $10k. Subsequently, sales were good and I even got married soon after üòÑ

So if you're having a tough start or hesitating because you're afraid of the hurdles, remember this: perseverance and readiness can turn even the smallest opportunity into a breakthrough. Keep pushing forward and your moment will come just like mine did!

Why Every Sales Professional Needs Systems

In the fast-paced world of sales, success does not come by chance. It comes by design. And one of the most powerful tools a salesperson can have is a system.

When we talk about systems in sales, we are referring to a structured approach. A repeatable, reliable process that guides how we find leads, nurture relationships, present solutions and close deals. It is about turning daily chaos into a well-oiled machine.

Why does this matter?

Because systems drive productivity. They save time, reduce stress and eliminate guesswork. They help us prioritize the right clients, follow up at the right time and track the right metrics. With systems in place, we do not just work harder. We work smarter.

Imagine knowing exactly what your next step is with every prospect. Imagine having automated follow-ups that go out like clockwork. Imagine being able to train new team members with ease because everything is already mapped out.

That is the power of systems
They bring consistency
They create scalability
And most importantly, they deliver results

Sales is not just an art. It is a science. And systems are what turn potential into performance.

If you are in sales and want to rise above the noise, build your systems

3 ùë®ùíÖùíóùíÇùíèùíïùíÇùíàùíÜùíî ùíêùíá ùë©ùíñùíöùíäùíèùíà ùë∞ùíèùíîùíñùíìùíÇùíèùíÑùíÜ ùë¨ùíÇùíìùíçùíö (ùíïùíâùíÇùíï ùíéùíêùíîùíï ùíëùíÜùíêùíëùíçùíÜ ùíÖùíêùíè'ùíï ùíåùíèùíêùíò ùíÇùíÉùíêùíñùíï) 

So, you're a young adult, right? 

It's great to be young and carefree, but as you start to take on more responsibilities and make your way in the world, some areas that we usually overlook is our physical and financial health. 

While I‚Äôm not a health coach or fitness trainer that can provide you the expertise‚Ä¶

I can help with the insurance portion ;P
 
It's not the most exciting topic‚Ä¶ but something you really can't afford to ignore. 

So, if you're ready to learn more about why insurance is important for young adults like you, dive into this post and explore the benefits of getting covered when you're young.

‚úÖCheaper Premiums When Younger
Did you know that you can lock in your premiums at cheaper prices? 

Life insurance premiums are based on several factors, including a person's health and age. Generally, the amount you pay to purchase a life insurance policy rises as you age. 

Rates can jump considerably if you wait until you are in your mid-thirties or forties due to the higher probability that the insurer will have to make a pay out on the policy you purchased. 

‚úÖGuarantee your Insurability 
Many people think they can buy insurance with money‚Ä¶.

Sorry to burst your bubble but unfortunately that isn't the case. 

You buy insurance primarily with your health. 

Almost ALL insurance policies have exemptions for pre-existing conditions, which means if you have a medical 
issue now, and buy insurance later, you won't be covered for that condition. 

The inevitable fact is that our health deteriorates as we age. Buying insurance when you're young and healthy lessens the need for medical check ups or more underwriting. We hope to be healthy forever but what if you and I are both wrong? Will it be too late?

‚úÖFinancial security in your Prime years ensures that you can focus on recuperating, even if it takes several years, without having to worry about paying for basic needs or family responsibilities.

And after almost 5 years in the industry, I can safely say, you will never be able to put a put a price tag on peace of mind

Part 1 
‚ú® Take Responsibility for Our Own Success ‚ú®

Just listened to the legendary Tony Gordon ‚Äî expelled from school at 16.
Written off by teachers. Doubted by friends.
Today, at 79, he stands as one of the greatest icons in the insurance world.
A true GOAT.

He ended his sharing with this powerful truth:

‚ÄúTake responsibility for our own success.
If things aren‚Äôt going our way‚Ä¶
Is it the company‚Äôs fault? Our manager‚Äôs fault? Other people‚Äôs fault?
NO‚Ä¶ HELL NO!‚Äù

That hit deep.

My biggest takeaway?
We‚Äôre not stuck.
We‚Äôre not stone.
We can move.
We can change.
We can find solutions.

‚ÄúWe are not a stone. We can move.‚Äù

So let‚Äôs:
‚û°Ô∏è Stop blaming
‚û°Ô∏è Stop pointing fingers
‚û°Ô∏è Keep moving
‚û°Ô∏è Keep failing forward
‚û°Ô∏è Keep growing
‚û°Ô∏è Keep becoming better

Every get-up brings us higher.
Let‚Äôs keep climbing ‚Äî together.

A very good reminder to self. - Part 1

Content_file1:
Part 2
Disclaimer: not trying to be disrespectful to anyone. Pardon the AI effect. 

‚ÄúSir, I just want to shake your hand.‚Äù
(He gave me a weird stare‚Ä¶ and a gentle smack on the arm.)

After listening to the legendary Tony Gordon‚Äîthe GOAT of the insurance industry‚Äîshare his story, I was deeply inspired.

At 79, he flew from the US to Malaysia just to spend an hour with us. He could‚Äôve stayed in the comfort of home, or travelled with friends. But he chose to be here‚Äîto give, to serve, to lift others. That alone taught me something: greatness doesn‚Äôt retire.

After his session, everyone rushed to take photos. I couldn‚Äôt get close, so I cheekily ‚Äúphoto bombed‚Äù and AI-ed myself closer in Photo 1.

But eventually, as the room cleared, we got a proper photo with him.

Then came my moment.
I walked up, extended my hand, and said:
‚ÄúSir, I just want to shake your hand.‚Äù

He looked at me with a confused stare‚Ä¶ then gave me a light smack on the arm.

I wasn‚Äôt trying to be cheeky or disrespectful.
I just wanted to feel the warmth of his hand.
To remind myself‚Äîhe‚Äôs human. Just like us.
Same warmth. Same heart. Same opportunity to do something great with our lives.

I‚Äôm grateful for this journey.
Grateful for the team and family we‚Äôve built at PFG.
And grateful even for the tough days‚Äîbecause they‚Äôre shaping us for something greater.

Let‚Äôs keep going.
Because if he can, we can.
If he did, so can we.

A good reminder to self. - Part 2

[13 April 2025 | Bali, Indonesia]

This year, I made a spontaneous decision by booking a solo trip to Bali for my birthday. Behind the spontaneity was a quiet need for something more - more clarity, more courage, more connection with myself. The thought of being alone in an unfamiliar place can be intimidating. But there‚Äôs no one to distract me, from me. And in that silence, I started to listen. I listened more‚Äîto the world around me and to myself. I noticed the little things: the art that spoke to me, dogs chasing waves, the sound of the ocean crashing onto shore. I confronted thoughts and feelings I usually drowned out with busyness. I learnt to appreciate my own pace, my own rhythm. I celebrated myself for the first time and celebrated with strangers who I may never meet again. And in all of that, I found a deep fulfilling sense of freedom ü´∂üèª

Success isn‚Äôt just about talent, hustle, or even luck. It‚Äôs about the systems you build around your goals.

Whether it‚Äôs your daily routine, your workflow, your fitness, or your client approach‚Äîbuild systems that support your long-term vision, not just your short-term wins.

The right system turns effort into results. It helps you grow, scale, and sustain success year after year.

Set goals, but build systems.
Because systems don‚Äôt rely on willpower‚Äîthey rely on design.

Wrapped up our Q1 review with an unforgettable offsite in Bangkok!
With our close-knit team, the planning sessions were focused and engaging with great conversations. Outside the meeting room, we soaked in the local culture‚Äî from exploring Talad Noi, the iconic Maeklong Railway Market, and the floating market, to making our first visit to the dreamy Bubble in the Forest Cafe.
We even tried out Muay Thai and learned to cook four classic Thai dishes in a fun, hands-on cooking class.
A perfect blend of culture, food, and fun! Here‚Äôs to a strong start to the year and more memories ahead!

Life‚Äôs Little Divine Connections

Met this young Indian lady recently‚Äîshe‚Äôs got a degree in Computer Science but is feeling stuck at a crossroad, unsure of her next step. From a total stranger, I had the chance to journey with her using the Enneagram and coaching card. It opened her eyes to the areas she can grow in, and gave her a clearer sense of direction.

Honestly, it filled me with so much joy! Even though I‚Äôm not from her industry, I‚Äôm thankful I could contribute by helping her build clarity, confidence, and values to guide her decisions.

Also want to give a shoutout to my coach @lilianong73 who‚Äôs been such a strong support in my own growth. Through her 5-day challenge, I gained fresh perspective, strategy and direction in my recruitment efforts. She truly complements my weaknesses and gives me the push I need.

We even got to celebrate our birthdays together‚Äîand as her coachee, I had the privilege of using the coaching card @jensensiaw to bless her back with clarity and purpose in her current season.

So grateful for these divine appointments. Life is meaningful when we can pour what we‚Äôve learned into others.

#EnneagramJourney #CoachingMoments #PurposeDriven #WomenSupportingWomen #DivineConnections #GrowthTogether#eqworld

All glory to God. For His grace, strength, and divine appointments every step of the way.

16 Years in the Business | 17 April 2025

I was just 21 when I RNF‚Äôd - wide-eyed, full of hope, with a simple dream: To make a real difference in people‚Äôs lives, especially the ones I loved.

I still remember what my leader‚Äôs mentor told me back then:
‚ÄúIf you do this right, with sincerity and service, you‚Äôll never run out of people to help.‚Äù

Back then, I had no idea how deeply this journey would shape me. I just knew I wanted to be someone others could count on.

Fast forward 16 years‚Ä¶
440 clients. Countless moments of courage, care, and conversation.

Still here.
Still growing.
Still giving from the heart.

Grateful for every person who‚Äôs been part of this story -
Clients who became friends, friends who became clients, mentors who saw more in me than I saw in myself and my tribe who‚Äôve stood by me through every season.

Here‚Äôs to the journey ahead.
The best is yet to come.

We were born free,
but from the moment we entered this world, labels quietly found their way onto us.

‚ÄúObedient,‚Äù ‚Äúclever,‚Äù ‚Äúaverage,‚Äù ‚Äúa failure‚Äù‚Ä¶
Society uses these labels to define worth,
and in our need for approval, we learned to conform ‚Äî
seeking validation under the weight of expectations.

But deep inside, we‚Äôve always been resisting.
The desire to truly be ourselves never disappeared ‚Äî just buried under layers of life.

One day, we begin to see clearly:
these labels were never who we really were.
We can choose to peel them off,
and become who we were meant to be.

True freedom isn‚Äôt reckless.
It‚Äôs choosing with awareness, growing with discipline,
and living by values we define for ourselves.

That is strength ‚Äî and a higher kind of freedom.

Alhamdulillah. Yesterday we had the honour of hosting our loved ones for Raya.

It wasn‚Äôt just an ordinary visit ‚Äî it held deep meaning for us.
29 and 27 years ago, my wife‚Äôs parents left (passed away) her and her siblings at a young age.
Since then, it was abang who stepped up ‚Äî carrying both roles ‚Äî always there to guide, support, and protect them like his own.

Being able to welcome him and his family into our home this Raya brought a different kind of warmth.
Seeing the kids ‚Äî the cucus ‚Äî laughing, playing, and bonding so naturally made us feel as if Ayah and Ibu were with us too, smiling over the gathering.

Moments like these remind me ‚Äî it‚Äôs not about how grand the house is or how lavish the spread.
It‚Äôs about the barakah in the hearts that fill the space.

Alhamdulillah for blessings that words sometimes cannot even describe.
